-- McDonald's to boost China investment 40 percent in 2011
-- 
-- Tue Dec 14, 2010 8:22pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/12/15/us-mcdonalds-idUSTRE6BE09720101215

 

 BEIJING  (Reuters) - McDonald's Corp ( MCD.N ) plans to increase its investment in China by 40 percent in 2011, primarily by opening 175-200 new restaurants in the country, the company said in a statement on Wednesday. 

 It did not provide details on the amount of the planned investment. (Reporting by Fang Yan and  Ken Wills )